header.gameNote: HOOPS FOR HOPE CLASSIC AT PUERTO VALLARTA MEXICO

article.headline: Jacksonville 71, Milwaukee 66
article.story: PUERTO VALLARTA, Mexico -- Dylan Fritsch scored 14 points to lead Jacksonville to a 71-66 win over Milwaukee on Saturday in the Hoops for Hope Classic. Fritsch was 5 of 10 from the field for the Dolphins (3-4). Jarvis Haywood scored 13 points and Glenn Powell added 10 points, nine rebounds. Milwaukee led early, but Jacksonville took a 15-14 lead in the first half and stay out front, despite shooting 35 percent from the field. The Dolphins scored 21 points off turnovers. The Panthers shot 43 percent from the field, but had 20 turnovers. Jordon Aaron led Milwaukee with 19 points. He had nine rebounds before fouling out of the game. Demetrius Harris scored 16 points and made 12 rebounds. James Haarsma finished with 10 points and seven rebounds. Thierno Niang added 10 for the Panthers (2-3).
